feat: model-agnostic chat history with auto-save and browser UI

- Conversations auto-save after every assistant reply (no manual save needed)
- Auto-save uses upsert — same conversation updates in place, no duplicates
- New conversation file format: id, title (from first user message), created_at,
  updated_at, origin_model, origin_endpoint, messages[]
- Messages are model-agnostic role/content pairs; any model can continue any chat
- New backend endpoints:
  - GET  /api/conversations/<id>  — load single conversation
  - DELETE /api/conversations/<id> — delete single conversation
  - DELETE /api/conversations      — delete all conversations
- Updated POST /api/save_conversation — now accepts id (upsert), model, endpoint
- Updated GET /api/conversations — returns title, origin_model, updated_at sorted newest-first
- New "Chat History" button in sidebar and collapsed icon strip
- History modal lists all saved chats: title, origin model, date, message count
- Load button restores full conversation; current model continues it unchanged
- Cross-model indicator shown in status bar when loading from a different model
- Delete individual or delete-all with confirmation dialogs
- Clear Chat resets currentConversationId so next chat starts as a new save

